  "texts": [
    "It is one of the most adaptable models for image synthesis thanks to the latter variants of the model, which could use the same theory to generate any data sample based on the distribution inputted to it.",
    "This is what specialised variants like CGAN, WGAN, WGAN-GP [70], LAPGAN [71], and InfoGAN specialise in doing.",
    "The SRGAN framework was the first to use a GAN model for SR and infer photo-realistic natural pictures for 4 upscaling factors.",
    "Three crucial SRGAN components were thoroughly researched by Wang et al., who then enhanced each one to create a better SRGAN with better visual quality named as ESRGAN [32].",
    "The notion of using proportional authenticity rather than absolute number to predict discriminator efficacy is borrowed from relativistic GANs [72], and is used in ESRGAN."
